      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "UNRWA USA demonstrates a robust capacity for scaling operations during crises, as shown by its <cite id=\"11\">113.8% three-year revenue CAGR</cite>. This growth is supported by a <cite id=\"12\">93.4% independent board of directors</cite>, ensuring strong oversight and governance. Their impact is quantifiable, with <cite id=\"13\">35,919 food parcels delivered</cite> in 2023 alone, alongside critical <cite id=\"14\">mental health and hospital support</cite> programs that address the psychological toll of displacement."
      ],
      "summary": "UNRWA USA National Committee is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization dedicated to supporting the humanitarian and developmental needs of Palestine refugees. The organization serves as a critical bridge between American donors and the UN agency for Palestine refugees, focusing on <cite id=\"1\">education, food assistance, and health services</cite> across the Gaza Strip, West Bank, Jordan, Lebanon, and Syria. In 2023, the organization experienced unprecedented growth, reporting <cite id=\"2\">$32,433,934 in total revenue</cite>, a significant increase from previous years driven by urgent humanitarian needs. UNRWA USA maintains an exceptional <cite id=\"3\">program expense ratio of 93.4%</cite> according to its latest filings, ensuring that every dollar donated is directed toward its mission. The organization is highly efficient in its operations, spending only <cite id=\"4\">$0.05 to raise every $1</cite>, which is well below industry averages for international relief. Beyond emergency aid, the organization invests in long-term human development, having provided <cite id=\"5\">100 university scholarships</cite> and repaired <cite id=\"6\">68 shelters</cite> in the most recent reporting period. Their commitment to transparency is evidenced by a <cite id=\"7\">95.5/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite> and a Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid.",
